Do you have between 2 and 4 years of experience? Are you eager to have an everlasting impact on clients? You are not afraid to be challenged intellectually and personally? Then you could be the one to strengthen our team.

Information
You will be part of an entrepreneurial team that focusses on providing high quality skills, technologies and advisory services. These can include data analytics strategy definition, business intelligence solution design, data transformation and visualization. By offering data-driven solutions, you will help clients to turn their data into meaningful insights.

As a Technology Consultant you will:
Focus on back-end and/or front-development of Business Analytics solutions;
Extract, clean and sample data to get suitable output for further analysis;
Coach colleagues on projects;
Make performance reports and data models to help make CXO-level decisions;
Conduct functional analysis and translate it into technical solutions

Requirements
Master Degree in the field of Business Economics, Business Analytics or Information Management;
Experience in consulting or service-oriented environments;
Experience in BI tools, preferably IBM Cognos, Tableau and/or Pentaho;
Proven success in contributing to a team-oriented environment;
Fluent in Dutch and/or French and English

Terms of employment
A no-nonsense working environment where you will evolve rapidly;
A team that is fun, eager-to-learn and eager-to-grow;
Excellent terms of employment;
The opportunity to focus on things that matter and make a difference;
Motivating salary including full range of extra-legal benefits

About Data Shift
The past few years, organizations have been considerably collecting data. This will only increase the coming years.

Until now, only the lucky few have truly succeeded in getting business value out of the data.

We know how to do this differently and succeed in shifting to a data-driven organization.

Our offer
Integration in a solid and dynamic team;
Possibility to participate in international projects;
Participation in exciting and motivating projects;
Career evolution;
New challenges.
Your role
Take active participation in Telecommunication international Project with data streams analysis;
SW Engineer will be people who have expertise in SW development for the language used in the area of the Advanced Analytics (Scala, Spark) and knowledge of the framework used in the scope of those developments (Spark, Kafka, H2O, Hadoop, Angular, etc);
Your profile
Min 2 years of professional experience in the Advanced Analytics domain;
Spark/Scala, Pyspark;
AWS, Microsoft Azure, G Cloud;
H2O.ai, Python Mlib, Scikit,React.js, Node.js, Mapbox, Qview, QSense, Tableau.
Fluent in English with knowledge of French or Dutch;

Data BI Specialist (m/f)
Departement: IT
Land: België

Regio: Brussel



As Data BI Specialist at LolaLiza you will be responsible for the quality of all data within LolaLiza and for the effectiveness of the reporting environment and analytical tools in support of business decision-making. In close collaboration with all the business departments (buying, retail, e-commerce, CRM, marketing, finance, logistics, …) you take the lead in creating a good data governance approach, modernizing our reporting tools and practices, and ensuring easy access to data which can be turned into valuable insights.

As a Data BI Specialist you will be under the direct responsibility of the IT Director and you will join a dynamic IT team of 10 people.

Are you an experienced Data BI Specialist with a passion for sales and customer data?
Do you like to link different systems into one data warehouse with one version of the truth?
Can you easily interpret and structure data and identify opportunities to leverage data?

If you mostly answered positively to the above questions, you should definitely keep on reading. You might be the next talent who will contribute to the future success story of LolaLiza!

Your main responsibilities as a Data BI Specialist at LolaLiza:

Manage projects related to company reporting from specifications to production;
Re-define the catalog of data for the various business departments of LolaLiza;
Carry the project of setting up a modern reporting tool (such as Power BI or Tableau);
Ensure the maintenance of existing tools and solutions, including IBM Cognos TM1;
Manage the relationship data with the internal departments;
Plan the complete scheduling of the diagnoses and interfaces within IT.
Who are you?
An experienced Data BI Specialist with several years of experience in a similar position (retail affinity is a plus);
You have a higher degree in IT and are passionate about the integration of reporting systems;
You like to work with numbers and data, and know how to create value from data. If you have an experience in statistical fields, it would be a plus;
You have a good level of project management and you know how to manage stakeholders;
You are proficient in SQL and have a knowledge of IBM Cognos TM1;
You are analytical, proactive and a real team player;
It would be great if you speak both French and Dutch since most of your colleagues do. But we talk a lot of English too and sometimes you might hear some Spanish, Greek, Slovac and German.
What we offer

A challenging and diverse position within an enthusiastic and dynamic organization;
The opportunity to develop yourself within a Belgian fashion company growing internationally;
You will start with an onboarding program so that you will know LolaLiza, our customers and the tools we use very well from the start;
An attractive salary package corresponding to your experience and your skills;
Staff discounts on the LolaLiza collections.

Interested?

Please mail me (Doreen van Bulck / doreen.vanbulck@ppretail.com) and I will tell you more about this challenging opportunity and/or help you with your questions.
